levels.helpHTML:
The version pairs are s6/s6j and peyg/peygj; the medalless level is bp.

The level groupings are mostly obvious; the movement group is intended to be hover-based/fluddless movement levels, and was defined in Nov 2020 as:

b3 b3s b4 b6 b6s r1 r2 r3 r4 r4s r5
g1s p2 p2s p3 p6s s2 s2s s3 s4 s4s
n1 n2 n6 n6s q3 q4 q6 c

best grate flips are irrelevant bc optimal cycles are pre-determined sadge

this gets 13.23 grate clip, which is the 3rd best optimal cycle. 12.93 is the next best, and WR gets 12.63. If you hit the grate one frame earlier than any of these (e.g. 13.20, 12.90), you lose 9 frames since you're stopping the fast ferris wheel slightly too early. Side note, it's probably just BARELY possible to make the cycle on a 13.26/12.96/12.66 cycle, which would save 0.3 on each respective cycle (i.e. save 0.3 on the WR)
